choices.text:
There are three killers in a room. Someone enters the room and kills one of them. Nobody leaves the room. How many killers are left in the room?
In this scenario, there were initially two human killers (assuming that only humans can be considered as "killers" here) and a third person who entered the room and killed one of the other individuals. So after the newcomer's action, there are still two remaining people in the room - both of whom could potentially be considered as "killers."
